headline: What Wells Fargo’s Credit Card Expansion Means for Stock Value in 2025
summary: Deciding what to do with Wells Fargo stock right now? You are not alone. With so much chatter around major banks, especially after a string of headlines, it is no wonder investors are itching for answers. Over the past year, Wells Fargo has rewarded the patient, boasting a 30.1% jump. If you zoom out to five years, the returns soar a whopping 280.7%. Yet, in the past month, the stock has slipped by 3.3%, adding a dose of realism to an otherwise strong rally. That recent dip might have caught...
